TV personality, Ayanda Thabethe, is the latest victim of a social media scams.In it, a fraudster has been using Ayanda&rsquo;s image to con unsuspecting fans.In the scam, victims are led to believe Ayanda is the brand ambassador for a sunglasses brand on the Instagram account, Larosa_sa, allegedly run by Bongani Mdaka.When contacted for comment, the star was shocked.&ldquo;I don&rsquo;t know the person running that Instagram account and would like to tell my fans not to fall for his trap,&rdquo; Ayanda said.&ldquo;I really hate what&rsquo;s going on behind my back, and will be pressing charges,&rdquo; she said.The first victim, who didn&rsquo;t want to be named, told the SunTeam she was lured into believing Larosa_sa was connected to Ayanda when inquiring about the sunglasses.&ldquo;After identifying himself as Bongani Mdaka, he gave me a quote for the shades I wanted,&rdquo; the victim said.&ldquo;He also sent a picture featuring Ayanda with the shades I wanted, coaxing me to add lipsticks and weaves, among other items, to the order.&ldquo;It&rsquo;s been a month since the purchase, and I have yet to receive my parcel.&ldquo;It&rsquo;s so sad that &lsquo;Bongani&rsquo; &ndash; or whoever he really is &ndash; no longer responds to my messages.&rdquo;The People&rsquo;s Paper has seen the Instagram DM (Direct Message) between the con man and the victim.Another casualty told Sunday Sun the con man was &ldquo;very methodical&rdquo; in his approach.Said the unsuspecting victim: &ldquo;He sent me a Capitec account to pay for the items.&ldquo;A lot of personalities&rsquo; images are being used without their consent.&rdquo;